<task id="013" project="spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Extend WorkspaceOptions.cs with 4 typed code options (CRIT-1 fix)</title>
    <phase>1: §1.7 Stable Codes Migration</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>010,011,012</dependencies>
    <blocks>014,015,016,017,018,019</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, config, ADR-018, architecture-binding</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Single sequential task that pre-seats typed options so wave 1-E parallel consumers don't collide on WorkspaceOptions.cs; CRIT-1 race-condition fix; tags include 'bff-api'; FULL per Step 0.5</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>1-B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>CRIT-1 fix: tasks 016, 017, 018, 019 would all edit WorkspaceOptions.cs in wave 1-E if extensions weren't pre-added; this single-agent task adds all 4 in one commit so wave 1-E is truly parallel-safe.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extend `WorkspaceOptions.cs` with 4 typed string options: `ChatSummarizePlaybookCode`, `MatterPreFillPlaybookCode`, `ProjectPreFillPlaybookCode`, and `AiSummaryPlaybookCode`. Bind each from `Workspace:&lt;Name&gt;` config section. Update `appsettings.Development.json` with the expected stable-code values. This task does NOT migrate any consumer — it ONLY pre-seats the typed options so wave 1-E (tasks 016–019) can complete in parallel without colliding on `WorkspaceOptions.cs`.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in IOptions binding + minimal-API DI. Coordinator role — enables downstream parallel migrations.</role>

  <goal>
    `WorkspaceOptions.cs` carries 4 new string properties (in addition to `SummarizePlaybookCode` from task 012). Each binds from the matching config section. Unit test asserts all 4 properties bind correctly. `appsettings.Development.json` has matching keys with expected stable-code values per spec §1.7.3 codes table.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per TASK-INDEX audit history CRIT-1: wave 1-E originally had 4 tasks (016, 017, 018, 019) all editing `WorkspaceOptions.cs` in parallel, creating a file-overlap race condition. The fix is to pre-add all 4 typed options in a single sequential task BEFORE wave 1-E. After this task, wave 1-E tasks only consume their respective typed option — they don't modify `WorkspaceOptions.cs`. Spec §1.7.3 codes table defines the four stable codes: `summarize-document-chat`, `create-matter-prefill`, `create-project-prefill`, and the `AiSummaryPlaybookCode` for `WorkspaceAiService`.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Options/WorkspaceOptions.cs</file>
      <file>config/appsettings.Development.json</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Options/WorkspaceOptionsTests.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">Typed options REQUIRED; properties have explicit defaults.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — no service registration changes; options bind via existing `services.Configure&lt;WorkspaceOptions&gt;()` from task 012.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement; expect ≤0.05 MB delta.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">§1.7.3 codes table — exact codes: `summarize-document-chat`, `create-matter-prefill`, `create-project-prefill`. `AiSummaryPlaybookCode` value to be confirmed during task 018 (deferred decision; default to existing playbook name).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">DO NOT modify any consumer in this task. Wave 1-E owns the consumer migrations.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Atomic commit — all 4 properties added in one PR/commit to satisfy CRIT-1 ordering invariant.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
